yÄ± geÄŸmiÅŸ. DÃ¼ÄŸÃ¼nde bulunanlardan birinin ÄŸocuÄŸu altÄ±nÄ± kirletmiÅŸ. Ã§ocuÄŸun annesi bez aramÄ±ÅŸ fakat bulamamÄ±ÅŸ. Ã§aresiz kalan anne ÄŸocuÄŸun aÄŸlamasÄ±na dayanamayarak yanÄ±nda bulunan yufka ekmeÄŸi ile altÄ±nÄ± temizlemiÅŸ. Bu olay sonucunda dÃ¼ÄŸÃ¼n alayÄ±nÄ±n tamamÄ± TanrÄ±nÄ±n gazabÄ±na uÄŸrayarak taÅŸ kesilmiÅŸtir. Bu efsaneye dayanÄ±larak bu daÄŸa Ã”Ã‡Â£Gelincik DaÄŸÄ±Ã”Ã‡Ã˜ denilmektedir.\r\n\r\n',NULL,0,'2026-02-22 09:52:36','Gelincik Mountain','Located 4 km northwest of Ã§ermik, Gelincik Mountain is approximately 1500 meters high. Known as the \"Cappadocia of Southeast Turkey\" due to its rock formations that resemble a human line when viewed from afar, it bears traces of the Paleolithic period. This natural wonder, with its dazzling beauty, captivates people and transports them to a world of fantasy. The rock formations, created by erosion from rainwater due to karst landforms, resemble the fairy chimneys of Cappadocia in Turkey. This mountain, which looks like a human line from a distance, also has a legend associated with it.\r\n\r\nThe Legend of Gelincik Mountain: Once upon a time, a wedding procession passed over this mountain. One of the children in the wedding party soiled their diaper. The child\'s mother searched for a diaper but couldn\'t find one. Helpless, unable to bear the child\'s crying, she cleaned the diaper with a piece of flatbread she had with her. As a result of this event, the entire wedding procession was struck by God\'s wrath and turned to stone. This mountain is called \"Poppy Mountain\" based on this legend.',''),(15,3,'Åeyhandede Åelalesi','Nature','Ã§ermik\'in Åeyhandede kÃ¶yÃ¼nde yer alan bu doÄŸa harikasÄ±, yaklaÅŸÄ±k 30 metre yÃ¼kseklikten dÃ¶kÃ¼lÃ¼r. Tabiat ParkÄ± statÃ¼sÃ¼ndedir ve derin bir vadi iÄŸerisinde Akdeniz kanyonlarÄ±nÄ± andÄ±ran bir yapÄ±ya sahiptir.\r\nÅeyhandede Åelalesi: Ä°smini ilÄŸeye 33 km uzaklÄ±kta bulunan Åeyhandede kÃ¶yÃ¼nden almaktadÄ±r. Åeyhandede KÃ¶prÃ¼sÃ¼Ã”Ã‡Ã–nden gÃ¼neye do