LL,0,'2026-02-22 09:52:36','Haburman Bridge','Built in 1179 during the Artukid period by ZÃ¼beyde Hatun, the bridge spans the Sinek Stream. With its three arches and limestone workmanship, it is a symbol of Artukid architecture. It is located on the Sinek Stream at the western exit of the district. It takes its name from Haburman Village, which is located to the west of the bridge. Made of large, hewn white stones, the bridge has a total of three arches, one of which is the main arch. Its length is 108 m, its width is 5.5 m, and its highest point is 12.5 m. This height decreases towards the edges. There are three inscriptions on the bridge walls. Two of them relate to its construction, and the other to its repair. The following can be read from this inscription:\r\n\r\nÃ”Ã‡Â£In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful. (This) was built with the help of Zubeyde Hatun, daughter of the esteemed Emir Najmuddin Albi, may Allah protect her. In the year 575 (1179)\r\nTurkish: In the name of Allah. This was built with the help of Zubeyde Hatun, daughter of the esteemed Emir Najmuddin Albi, may Allah protect her.\r\nFrom this inscription, it is understood that the Haburman Bridge was built by Zubeyde Hatun, daughter of Artuk\'s son Najmuddin Albi (1152-1176), three years after his death, during the reign of his brother Ilgazi II (1176-1184) and in the year 575 (1179). Considering the size of the bridge and the expenditure required, it is understood that in the period when the bridge was built...\" It is evident that this road was a very busy and important one. There are two important centers to the west of this road. It is known that the DiyarbakÄ±r-Aleppo road extends southwest over KaracadaÄŸ. In this case, the only important center that the road can reach via the bridge is Malatya.\r\n\r\nThe second inscription on the east side and south face of the bridge is damaged and cannot be read. From the few words that can be read in places, it is understood that the bridge was repaired in 1241 (1825-26).',''),(20,3,'Ulu Cami','Historical','Ulu Cami: Ä°lÄŸenin batÄ±sÄ±ndaki Kale MahallesiÃ”Ã‡Ã–nde bulunmaktadÄ±r. YapÄ± ayrÄ± zamanlarda inÅŸa edilmiÅŸ, bitiÅŸik iki camiden oluÅŸmaktadÄ±r. BatÄ± kesimi ilk yapÄ±dan kalmÄ±ÅŸ, doÄŸudaki tek kubbeli kÄ±sÄ±m ise sonradan ilave edilmiÅŸtir. DoÄŸudan batÄ±ya doÄŸru uzanan Ã¼ÄŸ tonoz ile Ã¼zeri kaplÄ± olan Ulu Cami, Ã¼ÄŸer kemerli iki sÄ±ra tonoz duvarlarÄ±yla iÄŸeriden bÃ¶lÃ¼nmÃ¼ÅŸtÃ¼r. BatÄ±da bulunan kapÄ±sÄ± orta tonusun altÄ±ndan aÄŸÄ±lmaktadÄ±r. \r\nUlu Caminin orta bÃ¶lÃ¼mÃ¼nde iki adet kitabe bulunmaktadÄ±r. YapÄ±lÄ±ÅŸ kitabesinde ÅŸu bilgiler yer almaktadÄ±r: \r\nÃ”Ã‡Ä°Ã”Ã‡Ä°CÃ¼ddede Ä°maretÃ”Ã‡Ã–Ã¼l - Mescid El Halid bi Ebubekr Ali bin El-hac â”œÃ»mer bin Mahmut. Fi seneti ErbaaÃ”Ã‡ÄÃ”Ã‡Ã˜\r\n	TÃ¼rkÄŸesi: Bunun yapÄ±lmasÄ±nÄ±n, efendi, malik, adil, nimetlerin sahibi Fahreddin Kara Arslan Bin Davut, Bin SÃ¶kmen, Bin Artuk - TanrÄ±nÄ±n rahmeti onun Ã¼zerine olsun- MÃ¼slÃ¼man cemaatinin koruyucusu, din uÄŸruna savaÅŸan Ä°laldÄ± BinÃ”Ã‡Ä.-TanrÄ±Ã”Ã‡Ä.devamlÄ± kÄ±lsÄ±n - emretti. \r\nYukarÄ±daki kitabede adÄ± geÄŸen Fahreddin Kara Arslan Bin Davut, Bin SÃ¶kmen, Bin Artuk seceresinde de anlaÅŸÄ±ldÄ±ÄŸÄ± gibi Artuklu HanedanÄ±nÄ±n HÄ±sn Keyfa koluna mensup olup, bu kolun 4. SultanÄ±dÄ±r. 539/1144-45 yÄ±lÄ±nda tahta geÄŸmiÅŸ ve 22 Ramazan 562/12 Temmuz 1167 de vefat ederek HÄ±sn KeyfaÃ”Ã‡Ã–da defnedilmiÅŸtir.\r\n	OnarÄ±m kitabesinin TÃ¼rkÄŸesi: Bu mescidi HacÄ± Halid Bin Ebubekir Ali Bin HacÄ± â”œÃ»mer Bin Mahmut 640/1242-43 yÄ±lÄ±nda onarmÄ±ÅŸtÄ±r.\r\n	Bu kitabelerden anlaÅŸÄ±lacaÄŸÄ± Ã¼zere Ulu Cami 539/1144-45 tarihinde HÄ±sn Keyfa (Hasan Keyf) ArtuklularÄ±ndan Fahreddin Kara Arslan zamanÄ±nda, Ä°naloÄŸullarÄ±ndan Ebu Mansur Ä°laldÄ± Bin Ä°brahim tarafÄ±ndan inÅŸa ettirilmiÅŸtir. YaklaÅŸÄ±k olarak 100 yÄ±l sonra 640(1240-43) yÄ±lÄ±nda HacÄ± Halid Bin Ebubekir adÄ±nda bir zat caminin harap olan kÄ±sÄ±mlarÄ±nÄ± onarmÄ±ÅŸtÄ±r.\r\n	MoÄŸol istilasÄ± sonucu tahrip olan cami 1297-1302