the bathhouse.\r\n\r\nThe building\'s exterior walls are constructed of rubble stone. A pool is located in the center of the changing room. A doorway with a low arch to the northwest of the changing room leads to another rectangular space. A broken-arched vault extending east-west covers this space. There is a skylight on the west wall of this space, and a skylight lantern on top of the vault. From here, a doorway of the same type leads to another rectangular space covered by a broken-arched vault. On the east side of this space, a semi-octagonal iwan covered with a segmented semi-dome attracts attention. A low-arched doorway in the northwest corner opens to the hot room. Along the side walls are iwans, and bathing cells are located in the corners. The iwans are covered with broken-arched vaults. The floors of the changing room and other areas are covered with cobblestones.',''),(24,3,'Karakaya HanÄ±','Historical','Tarihi Ä°pek Yolu Ã¼zerinde, kervanlarÄ±n konaklamasÄ± iÄŸin Anadolu SelÄŸuklu dÃ¶neminde inÅŸa edilmiÅŸtir. 700 yÄ±llÄ±k bu han, restorasyon sonrasÄ± turizme kazandÄ±rÄ±lmÄ±ÅŸtÄ±r.\r\nÃ§ermik Ä°lÄŸe merkezine 25 km. gÃ¼neybatÄ±sÄ±nda yer alan Karakaya KÃ¶yÃ¼nde bulunmaktadÄ±r. Han, kuzey-gÃ¼ney uzanan genel hatlarÄ±yla dikdÃ¶rtgen bir yapÄ±dÄ±r. TaÅŸ kapÄ±sÄ± gÃ¼ney kÄ±smÄ±ndadÄ±r. YapÄ± iki sÄ±ra halinde dÃ¼zenlenmiÅŸ sekiz adet taÅŸ paye ile Ã¼ÄŸ sahÄ±na bÃ¶lÃ¼nmÃ¼ÅŸtÃ¼r. Kuzey-gÃ¼ney yÃ¶nÃ¼nde uzanan sahÄ±nlar hafif sivri kemerli tonozlarla Ã¶rtÃ¼lÃ¼dÃ¼r. YapÄ±nÄ±n tamamÄ± dÃ¼zgÃ¼n sÄ±ralar halinde dizilmiÅŸ kÄ±rma taÅŸlarla inÅŸa edilmiÅŸtir. TonozlarÄ±n inÅŸasÄ±nda ise yassÄ± taÅŸ plakalar kullanÄ±lmÄ±ÅŸtÄ±r. YapÄ±lan araÅŸtÄ±rmalarda avlusuz SelÄŸuklu HanlarÄ±nÄ±n geÄŸ devir eseri olduÄŸu belirtilen Karakaya HanÄ± XIII yy sonlarÄ± ile XIV yy baÅŸlarÄ±na tarihlenmektedir.','','38.06058258241191','39.30632683708964','assets/img/places/han.jpg','','','Ä°pek Yolu kervanlarÄ±nÄ±n hikayelerini ve hanÄ±n mimari saÄŸlamlÄ±ÄŸÄ±nÄ± anlat.\r\nÃ§ermik Ä°lÄŸe m