hurch ruins near the castle represent the mosaic of faiths in the region. Synagogue: In the Kale neighborhood of our district, there is a synagogue dating back to the Jewish community. Completely constructed from black and white basalt stones, the synagogue\'s exact age is unknown. Currently used as a house, this structure consists of a single section. An inscription, presumably in Hebrew, is located on the building. Of the two arched sections side-by-side on the exterior, the left contains the original water system. The room inside the synagogue has niches. A three-arched section with two columns divides the room into two.\r\n\r\nChurch: Part of the church is now used as a house. It is in ruins. It is unknown when and by whom it was built. There are Armenian inscriptions on the stones of the house. The presence of a mosque, church, and synagogue side-by-side in the district is the best evidence that people of various religions have lived together in our district since ancient times.',''),(26,5,'Karakaya BarajÄ±','HotSpring','DiyarbakÄ±râ€™Ä±n Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ ilÃ§esi sÄ±nÄ±rlarÄ±nda yer alan Karakaya BarajÄ±, sadece bÃ¶lgenin deÄŸil, TÃ¼rkiyeâ€™nin Cumhuriyet tarihindeki en bÃ¼yÃ¼k mÃ¼hendislik baÅŸarÄ±larÄ±ndan biri olarak kabul edilir. GÃ¼neydoÄŸu Anadolu Projesiâ€™nin (GAP) kilit taÅŸlarÄ±ndan biri olan bu dev yapÄ±nÄ±n tarihÃ§esi, TÃ¼rkiye\'nin enerji baÄŸÄ±msÄ±zlÄ±ÄŸÄ± yolculuÄŸunu simgeler.Ä°ÅŸte Karakaya BarajÄ±â€™nÄ±n planlanmasÄ±ndan bugÃ¼ne uzanan detaylÄ± tarihi sÃ¼reci:1. Planlama ve Proje AÅŸamasÄ± (1960\'lar - 1970\'ler)Karakaya projesinin kÃ¶kleri, FÄ±rat Nehri\'nin potansiyelini deÄŸerlendirmek amacÄ±yla yapÄ±lan geniÅŸ Ã§aplÄ± araÅŸtÄ±rmalara dayanÄ±r.KeÅŸif: FÄ±rat Nehri Ã¼zerinde bir \"barajlar dizisi\" kurulmasÄ± fikri 1960â€™lÄ± yÄ±llarda olgunlaÅŸmaya baÅŸladÄ±.EtÃ¼t Ã‡alÄ±ÅŸmalarÄ±: Elektrik Ä°ÅŸleri EtÃ¼t Ä°daresi (EÄ°EÄ°) tarafÄ±ndan yapÄ±lan incelemelerde, Karakaya BoÄŸazÄ±\'nÄ±n dar ve derin yapÄ±sÄ±nÄ±n, yÃ¼ksek gÃ¶vdeli bir baraj inÅŸa etmek 