y! Here is the detailed historical information about the Karakaya Dam in English, organized for clarity.Detailed History of the Karakaya Dam (Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ)Located within the borders of the Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ district in DiyarbakÄ±r, the Karakaya Dam is considered one of the greatest engineering achievements in the history of the Turkish Republic. As a cornerstone of the Southeastern Anatolia Project (GAP), its history symbolizes Turkey\'s journey toward energy independence.1. Planning and Project Phase (1960s â€“ 1970s)The roots of the Karakaya project lie in extensive research conducted to harness the potential of the Euphrates River.Discovery: The idea of creating a \"cascade of dams\" on the Euphrates began to mature in the 1960s.Feasibility Studies: Investigations by the General Directorate of Electrical Power Resources Survey and Development Administration (EÄ°EÄ°) identified the Karakaya Gorgeâ€”with its narrow and deep structureâ€”as the most geologically suitable point for a high-body dam.Political Will: By the early 1970s, the technical details were finalized, and it was designated as a priority investment within the GAP framework.2. Construction Process (1976 â€“ 1987)The construction of the Karakaya Dam is often described as an \"engineering epic,\" considering the limited resources of the era and the challenging geography.Groundbreaking: Construction officially began in 1976.International Cooperation: The project was carried out by a consortium of Italian and Turkish firms. Financing was secured through the World Bank and various European credit agencies.Technical Challenges: Diverting the high-flow Euphrates River and pouring concrete onto steep cliffs required years of meticulous labor.3. Opening and CommissioningThe completion of the dam was a historic turning point in addressing Turkey\'s energy deficit.Impoundment (Water Retention): The reservoir began filling in 1986. During this process, several settlements and historical sites in the region were submerged.Official Opening: The Karakaya Dam and Hydroelectric Power Plant (HEPP) were officially inaugurated on March 13, 1987, by the Prime Minister of the time, Turgut Ã–zal.Full Capacity: By 1989, all units were operational, meeting approximately 20% of Turkey\'s total electricity needs at that time.Technical and Historical HighlightsFeatureDetailDam TypeConcrete, double-curvature Thin Arch (a rare example in Turkey).Height173 meters from the foundation.Energy Capacity1,800 MW installed capacity, producing an average of 7.35 billion kWh annually.AwardsReceived international recognition in the 1980s for architectural and engineering excellence.4. Cultural and Social ImpactThe dam\'s construction was more than just a technical feat; it brought about socio-cultural shifts:Karakaya Railway Bridge: Built over the reservoir, this bridge connects Malatya and ElazÄ±ÄŸ and is one of the longest railway bridges in Turkey.Archaeological Rescue: Before the reservoir was filled, rescue excavations were conducted at important Neolithic sites like Cafer HÃ¶yÃ¼k, shedding light on early human history.Key Fact: To this day, Karakaya remains the second-most powerful energy-producing facility on the Euphrates River after the AtatÃ¼rk Dam.','The Strategic Value of Karakaya Dam to the National Energy Grid\r\nKarakaya is one of the \"golden rings\" on the Euphrates River. It maintains its title as Turkeyâ€™s second-largest hydroelectric power plant, following the AtatÃ¼rk Dam.\r\n\r\nInstalled Capacity: 1,800 MW (consisting of 6 units, each with a capacity of 300 MW).\r\n\r\nAnnual Production: It generates an average of 7.3 billion kWh (kilowatt-hours) of electricity.\r\n\r\nCoverage Area: This output is a massive force capable of single-handedly meeting the annual electricity needs of approximately 2.1 million households or about 8 districts with a population of 250,000 each.\r\n\r\n2025â€“2028 Rehabilitation and Efficiency Increase\r\nA historic renovation process is currently underway at the dam. This \"local and national\" touch, carried out through the collaboration of EÃœAÅ (Electricity Generation Corp.) and TEMSAN (Turkish Electromechanical Industries), yields the following results:\r\n\r\nEfficiency Boost: The efficiency of the turbines is being increased from 91% to over 95%.\r\n\r\nAdditional Production: This modernization alone will generate an extra 178 GWh of electricity every year.\r\n\r\nFinancial Gain: This additional production will contribute approximately 510 million TL (at 2025â€“2026 values) annually to the national economy.'),(27,3,'15 Temmuz ParkÄ±','','DiyarbakÄ±r\'Ä±n Ã§ermik ilÄŸesinde bulunan 15 Temmuz Åehitler ParkÄ±, ilÄŸenin en Ã¶nemli sosyal donatÄ± ve mesire alanlarÄ±ndan biridir. ParkÄ±n genel Ã¶zellikleri ve Ã¶ne ÄŸÄ±kan tarihi dÃ¶nÃ¼ÅŸÃ¼mÃ¼ hakkÄ±nda bilmen gereken detaylar ÅŸunlardÄ±r:\r\n\r\nGenel Bilgi ve Konum\r\nKonum: Ã§ermik ilÄŸesinin kuzey kÄ±smÄ±nda, Tepe Mahallesi sÄ±nÄ±rlarÄ± iÄŸerisinde ve Ã§Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ karayolu Ã¼zerinde yer almaktadÄ±r.\r\n\r\nSeyirtepe â”œÃ»zelliÄŸi: Konumu itibarÄ±yla ilÄŸeye yÃ¼ksekten bakan bir noktada bulunduÄŸu iÄŸin halk arasÄ±nda \"Seyirtepe\" olarak da adlandÄ±rÄ±lÄ±r. Bu sayede ziyaretÄŸilerine muazzam bir ilÄŸe ve doÄŸa manzarasÄ± sunar.\r\n\r\nBÃ¼yÃ¼klÃ¼k: YaklaÅŸÄ±k 33,7 dÃ¶nÃ¼mlÃ¼k (33.700 metrekare) devasa bir alan Ã¼zerine kurulmuÅŸtur ve bu yÃ¶nÃ¼yle ilÄŸeye kazandÄ±rÄ±lmÄ±ÅŸ en bÃ¼yÃ¼k parklardan biridir.\r\n\r\nÃ§arpÄ±cÄ± Bir \"Kentsel DÃ¶nÃ¼ÅŸÃ¼m\" Hikayesi\r\nParkÄ±n bulunduÄŸu alan, yapÄ±mÄ±ndan Ã¶nce yaklaÅŸÄ±k 30 yÄ±l boyunca ilÄŸenin vahÅŸi ÄŸÃ¶p dÃ¶kÃ¼m alanÄ± olarak kullanÄ±lÄ±yordu. YayÄ±lan aÄŸÄ±r koku ve duman hem Ã§ermik hem de Ã§Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ halkÄ±nÄ± ciddi ÅŸekilde rahatsÄ±z ediyordu.\r\n\r\n2017 YÄ±lÄ±ndaki Proje: Ã§ermik Belediyesi, 2017 yÄ±lÄ±nda ÄŸÃ¶p alanÄ±nÄ± ilÄŸe merkezinden 1,5 kilometre uzaÄŸa taÅŸÄ±yarak bu 30 yÄ±llÄ±k sorunu ÄŸÃ¶zdÃ¼.\r\n\r\nMÃ¼hendislik Ã§alÄ±ÅŸmasÄ±: Eski ÄŸÃ¶p alanÄ±nÄ±n parka dÃ¶nÃ¼ÅŸtÃ¼rÃ¼lmesi sÃ¼recinde, toprak altÄ±nda metan