tually complementary elements:\r\n\r\nMicroclimate Effect: The presence of the Euphrates River and the dam lake moderates the climate in and around Karakaya Village. This allows for the cultivation of a wider variety of fruits and vegetables (such as pomegranates and figs) in the region, unlike the rest of DiyarbakÄ±r.\r\n\r\nThe Italian Village Story: The fact that thousands of Italian engineers and workers lived in the region during the construction of the Karakaya Dam (1976-1987) added very interesting cultural layers to this geography on the banks of the Euphrates, such as the \"Italian Village\".',''),(40,3,'KuruyemiÅŸ PazarÄ±','Kuruyemis','Ã‡ermik ilÃ§e merkezinde bulunan bu pazar, Ã¶zellikle bÃ¶lgenin en Ã¶nemli geÃ§im kaynaklarÄ±ndan biri olan baÄŸcÄ±lÄ±k ve kuruyemiÅŸ kÃ¼ltÃ¼rÃ¼nÃ¼n sergilendiÄŸi yerdir. Yerel halkÄ±n ve kaplÄ±ca ziyaretÃ§ilerinin en uÄŸrak noktalarÄ±ndan biridir.\r\n\r\nÃ–ne Ã‡Ä±kan ÃœrÃ¼nler:\r\n\r\nÃ‡ermik Karadutu: Hem kurusu hem de pekmeziyle Ã¼nlÃ¼dÃ¼r. Åifa kaynaÄŸÄ± olarak bilinir.\r\n\r\nBadem ve Ceviz: BÃ¶lgenin daÄŸlÄ±k kÃ¶ylerinde yetiÅŸen, ince kabuklu ve yÃ¼ksek yaÄŸ oranlÄ± yerli bademler (el bademi) ve cevizler burada bÃ¼yÃ¼k ilgi gÃ¶rÃ¼r.\r\n\r\nÃœzÃ¼m ve TÃ¼revleri: Kuru Ã¼zÃ¼m, pestil, muska ve meÅŸhur Ã‡ermik pekmezi pazarÄ±n temel taÅŸlarÄ±dÄ±r. Ã–zellikle kÄ±ÅŸ aylarÄ±nda enerji kaynaÄŸÄ± olarak tÃ¼ketilen \"kesme\" ve \"sucuk\" (cevizli sucuk) en Ã§ok satÄ±lan Ã¼rÃ¼nler arasÄ±ndadÄ±r.\r\n\r\nKavun Ã‡ekirdeÄŸi: Ã‡ermik\'e has bir gelenek olarak kavun Ã§ekirdekleri kurutulup kavrularak kuruyemiÅŸ olarak tÃ¼ketilir.\r\n\r\nÃ–nemi:\r\nPazar, sadece bir alÄ±ÅŸveriÅŸ noktasÄ± deÄŸil, aynÄ± zamanda kÃ¶ylÃ¼lerin el emeÄŸi Ã¼rÃ¼nlerini doÄŸrudan tÃ¼keticiye ulaÅŸtÄ±rdÄ±ÄŸÄ± bir ekonomik dÃ¶ngÃ¼ merkezidir. KaplÄ±caya gelen turistler iÃ§in ise Ã‡ermik\'ten gÃ¶tÃ¼rÃ¼lecek en gÃ¼zel hediyelik eÅŸya bu doÄŸal lezzetlerdir.','','38.13564405666003','39.44860830833946','','','','',NULL,0,'2026-03-10 09:23:22','Ã‡ermik Dried Fruit and Nut Market ','Located in the district center of Ã‡ermik, this market is the heart of the region\'s viticulture (grape-growing) and dried fruit culture. It is one of the most popular spots for both locals and visitors who come for the thermal springs.\r\n\r\nFeatured Products:\r\n\r\nÃ‡ermik Black Mulberry: Famous for its dried form and molasses (pekmez). It is highly regarded as a source of healing.\r\n\r\nAlmonds and Walnuts: Native \"paper-shell\" almonds and high-fat walnuts grown in the mountainous villages of the district are highly sought after.\r\n\r\nGrapes and Derivatives: Raisins, fruit leathers (pestil), fruit amulets (muska), and the famous Ã‡ermik molasses are the staples of the market. \"Kesme\" and \"Cevizli Sucuk\" (walnut sausage/churchkhela) are top sellers, especially as energy sources during winter.\r\n\r\nMelon Seeds: A unique Ã‡ermik tradition involves drying and roasting melon seeds to be consumed as a snack.\r\n\r\nSignificance:\r\nThe market is not just a shopping destination; it is an economic hub where villagers bring their handmade products directly to the consumer. For tourists visiting the hot springs, these natural delicacies are the most authentic souvenirs to bring back from Ã‡ermik.',''),(41,5,'KuruyemiÅŸ PazarÄ±','Kuruyemis','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'2026-03-10 09:23:22',NULL,NULL,NULL),(43,5,'Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ Ermeni Kilisesi','Historical','Ä°lÃ§e merkezinde bulunan ve gÃ¶rkemli taÅŸ iÅŸÃ§iliÄŸiyle dikkat Ã§eken en Ã¶nemli tarihi yapÄ±dÄ±r. BÃ¼yÃ¼k oranda tahrip olmuÅŸ olsa da devasa duvarlarÄ± ve mimari detaylarÄ± hala etkileyicidir.\r\n\r\nTarihÃ§e ve Genel Bilgi:\r\nÃ‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ ilÃ§e merkezinde yer alan bu yapÄ±, aslÄ±nda bÃ¼yÃ¼k bir manastÄ±r kompleksinin ana kilisesidir. Ermeni mirasÄ±na ait olan bu yapÄ±, bÃ¶lgedeki Hristiyan nÃ¼fusun yoÄŸun olduÄŸu dÃ¶nemlerde eÄŸitim ve ibadet merkezi olarak kullanÄ±lmÄ±ÅŸtÄ±r.\r\n\r\nMimari Ã–zellikler:\r\n\r\nÄ°nÅŸa Malzemesi: BÃ¶lgenin karakteristik siyah bazalt taÅŸÄ± ve 