 there have been discussions regarding its restoration and preservation to integrate it into the regionâ€™s cultural and faith tourism.',''),(44,5,'Ali Bey Camii','Historical','OsmanlÄ± dÃ¶nemine ait olan bu cami, \r\n\r\nÃ‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ ilÃ§e merkezinde yer alan cami, klasik OsmanlÄ± mimarisinin bÃ¶lgeye has Ã¶zelliklerle harmanlandÄ±ÄŸÄ± bir eserdir. Mimari yapÄ±sÄ± ve sÃ¼slemeleriyle DiyarbakÄ±r genelindeki cami kÃ¼ltÃ¼rÃ¼nÃ¼n Ã¶nemli bir parÃ§asÄ±dÄ±r.\r\n\r\nMimari Ã–zellikler:\r\n\r\nÄ°nÅŸa Tarihi: Tam yapÄ±m tarihi net olarak bilinmese de, mimari tarzÄ± ve vakfiyeler 19. yÃ¼zyÄ±l baÅŸlarÄ±nÄ± (OsmanlÄ± DÃ¶nemi) iÅŸaret etmektedir. BazÄ± kaynaklara gÃ¶re daha eski temeller Ã¼zerine inÅŸa edilmiÅŸ olabilir.\r\n\r\nMalzeme: YapÄ±mda bÃ¶lgeye Ã¶zgÃ¼ siyah bazalt taÅŸÄ± ve kalker (beyaz taÅŸ) kullanÄ±lmÄ±ÅŸtÄ±r. Bu, camiye hem dayanÄ±klÄ±lÄ±k hem de estetik bir kontrast kazandÄ±rÄ±r.\r\n\r\nMinare: Cami, tek ÅŸerefeli, silindirik ve oldukÃ§a estetik bir minareye sahiptir. Minare gÃ¶vdesinde taÅŸ iÅŸÃ§iliÄŸi dikkat Ã§eker.\r\n\r\nPlan: Kareye yakÄ±n bir plana sahip olan caminin iÃ§ mekanÄ±, sade ama huzurlu bir atmosfere sahiptir. AhÅŸap tavan iÅŸlemeleri ve kemerli pencereleri bÃ¶lgenin ruhunu yansÄ±tÄ±r.\r\n\r\nÃ–nemi:\r\nÄ°lÃ§edeki sosyal hayatÄ±n merkezi olmuÅŸ, tarih boyunca sadece bir ibadethane deÄŸil, aynÄ± zamanda bir toplanma ve eÄŸitim merkezi olarak da kullanÄ±lmÄ±ÅŸtÄ±r.Ã¶lgedeki klasik Ä°slam mimarisinin zarif Ã¶rneklerinden biridir. VakÄ±f kayÄ±tlarÄ±na gÃ¶re oldukÃ§a eski bir geÃ§miÅŸe sahiptir.','','38.212327850438164','39.28757272737012','uploads/places/place_1773225082_4544.jpg','','','',NULL,0,'2026-03-11 05:59:57','','General Information:\r\nLocated in the center of the Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ district in DiyarbakÄ±r, the Ali Bey Mosque is one of the most significant historical landmarks in the region. It represents a blend of classical Ottoman architecture with local artistic touches.\r\n\r\nArchitectural Features:\r\n\r\nConstruction Date: Although the exact date of construction is not definitively documented, its architectural style and endowments suggest the early 19th century (Ottoman Era). Some historians believe it may have been built over an even older foundation.\r\n\r\nMaterials: The mosque was built using local black basalt stone and limestone (white stone). This combination provides both structural durability and a striking aesthetic contrast typical of DiyarbakÄ±r\'s architecture.\r\n\r\nMinaret: It features a single-balcony, cylindrical minaret that is notably elegant. The stone masonry on the minaret body is particularly detailed.\r\n\r\nLayout: The interior has a near-square plan, offering a simple yet serene atmosphere. The wooden ceiling decorations and arched windows reflect the traditional craftsmanship of the region.\r\n\r\nSignificance:\r\nAs a central hub for social life in the district, Ali Bey Mosque has served not only as a place of worship but also as a community gathering and educational center throughout history.',''),(45,5,'Tarihi Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ KÃ¶prÃ¼sÃ¼','Historical','Ä°lÃ§e merkezine yakÄ±n bir noktada, Ã§ay Ã¼zerinde kurulu olan bu taÅŸ kÃ¶prÃ¼, bÃ¶lgenin eski ticaret yollarÄ± Ã¼zerindeki geÃ§iÅŸ gÃ¼zergahÄ±nÄ± simgeler.\r\nGenel Bilgi:\r\nÃ‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ KÃ¶prÃ¼sÃ¼, ilÃ§enin giriÅŸinde veya yakÄ±n Ã§evresindeki akarsular Ã¼zerinde bulunan, OsmanlÄ± dÃ¶nemine tarihlendirilen bir yapÄ±dÄ±r. BÃ¶lgedeki kervan yollarÄ±nÄ±n ve yerel ulaÅŸÄ±mÄ±n can damarÄ± olmuÅŸtur.\r\n\r\nMimari Ã–zellikler:\r\n\r\nYapÄ±m TarzÄ±: Klasik OsmanlÄ± kÃ¶prÃ¼ mimarisinin Ã¶zelliklerini taÅŸÄ±r. Genellikle tek kemerli veya arazinin durumuna gÃ¶re iki kemerli olarak inÅŸa edilmiÅŸtir.\r\n\r\nMalzeme: YapÄ±mÄ±nda bÃ¶lgeye Ã¶zgÃ¼, suya dayanÄ±klÄ± siyah bazalt taÅŸÄ± ve kalker kullanÄ±lmÄ±ÅŸtÄ±r. Kemer kÄ±smÄ±ndaki taÅŸ iÅŸÃ§iliÄŸi, kÃ¶prÃ¼nÃ¼n yÃ¼k taÅŸÄ±ma kapasitesini artÄ±racak ÅŸekilde hassas bir mÃ¼hendislikle yerleÅŸtirilmiÅŸtir.\r\n\r\nForm: KÃ¶prÃ¼nÃ¼n formu, taÅŸkÄ±n zamanlarÄ±nda suyun geÃ§iÅŸini kolaylaÅŸtÄ±rmak iÃ§in hafif \"deve sÄ±rtÄ±\" (eÄŸimli) bir yapÄ±ya sahiptir.\r\n\r\nÃ–nemi:\r\nKÃ¶prÃ¼, sadece bir geÃ§iÅŸ noktasÄ± deÄŸil, aynÄ± zamanda Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸâ€™Ã¼n izolasyonunu kÄ±ran ve onu dÄ±ÅŸ dÃ¼nyaya baÄŸlayan tarihi bir semboldÃ¼r. GÃ¼nÃ¼mÃ¼zde modern kÃ¶prÃ¼ler yapÄ±lsa da, bu tarihi kÃ¶prÃ¼ hala ayaktadÄ±r.','','38.21264830960675','39.290152696690896','uploads/places/place_1773225263_8787.jpg','','','',NULL,0,'2026-03-11 06:00:15','','General Information:\r\nThe Historical Bridge of Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ, situated over the streams that feed into the Euphrates River, is a structure dating back to the Ottoman era. It served as a vital artery for local transportation and historical caravan routes in this rugged terrain.\r\n\r\nArchitectural Features:\r\n\r\nConstruction Style: It bears the hallmarks of classical Ottoman bridge architecture. Depending on the terrain, it was constructed with either a single arch or double arches.\r\n\r\nMaterials: High-quality, water-resistant local black basalt and limestone were used in its construction. The masonry work on the arch reflects precise engineering designed to maximize load-bearing capacity.\r\n\r\nForm: The bridge features a slight \"humpback\" (sloped) design, a common historical architectural choice to facilitate water flow during flood seasons.\r\n\r\nSignificance:\r\nMore than just a crossing point, this bridge is a historical symbol that broke the isolation of Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ, connecting it to the outer world. Despite the construction of modern bridges nearby, this historical structure stands as a testament to the region\'s enduring craftsmanship.',''),(46,5,'Eski Hamam','Historical','OsmanlÄ± dÃ¶neminden kalma, kesme taÅŸlarla inÅŸa edilmiÅŸ geleneksel bir TÃ¼rk hamamÄ±dÄ±r.\r\nDiyarbakÄ±râ€™Ä±n Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ ilÃ§esinde bulunan tarihi hamam, ilÃ§enin Orta Ã‡aÄŸ\'dan OsmanlÄ± dÃ¶nemine uzanan kÃ¶klÃ¼ geÃ§miÅŸinin en Ã¶nemli sosyal yapÄ±larÄ±ndan biridir. Halk arasÄ±nda genellikle Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ Tarihi HamamÄ± olarak bilinen bu yapÄ±, klasik