Artuqid foundations.\r\n\r\nArchitectural Features:\r\n\r\nBuilding Materials: The structure was built using black basalt stone and rubble stone, reflecting the characteristic architectural identity of the DiyarbakÄ±r region.\r\n\r\nSections: It consists of the traditional Ottoman bath layout: the \"SoyunmalÄ±k\" (changing/cold room), the \"IlÄ±klÄ±k\" (warm room), and the \"SÄ±caklÄ±k\" (hot room).\r\n\r\nDome Structure: The central hot room is covered by a large dome. Natural light enters through small circular glass openings on the dome, known as \"elephant eyes\" (fil gÃ¶zÃ¼).\r\n\r\nWater System: Historically, the bathâ€™s water was supplied from the districtâ€™s natural springs via ancient stone channels.\r\n\r\nCurrent Status:\r\nHaving suffered from neglect over the years and being used as a warehouse for a period, the bath is now a focus of restoration efforts by local authorities to preserve it as a cultural heritage site. It remains a vital stop on the historical tour of Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ.',''),(47,5,'Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ KonaklarÄ±','Historical','Dar sokaklarda yer alan, bazalt ve kalker taÅŸÄ±ndan yapÄ±lmÄ±ÅŸ geleneksel evler, bÃ¶lgenin sivil mimarisini yansÄ±tÄ±r.\r\nGenel Bilgi:\r\nÃ‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ konaklarÄ±, genellikle 19. yÃ¼zyÄ±l ve 20. yÃ¼zyÄ±l baÅŸlarÄ±na tarihlenen, bÃ¶lgenin varlÄ±klÄ± aileleri, yerel yÃ¶neticileri veya tÃ¼ccarlarÄ± tarafÄ±ndan yaptÄ±rÄ±lan Ã§ok katlÄ± yapÄ±lardÄ±r. Bu konaklar, ilÃ§enin dik yamaÃ§larÄ±na uyum saÄŸlayacak ÅŸekilde teraslanarak inÅŸa edilmiÅŸtir.\r\n\r\nMimari Ã–zellikler:\r\n\r\nMalzeme: Ana yapÄ± malzemesi, DiyarbakÄ±r genelinde olduÄŸu gibi siyah bazalt taÅŸÄ± ve beyaz kalkerdir. Bu iki rengin uyumu cephelerde estetik bir gÃ¶rÃ¼nÃ¼m saÄŸlar.\r\n\r\nPlan ÅemasÄ±: Genellikle iki veya Ã¼Ã§ katlÄ±dÄ±rlar. Alt katlar kÄ±ÅŸlÄ±k oda, kiler ve ahÄ±r olarak kullanÄ±lÄ±rken; Ã¼st katlar yazlÄ±k odalar, geniÅŸ pencereler ve manzaraya hakim balkonlarla (eyvan benzeri Ã§Ä±kmalar) donatÄ±lmÄ±ÅŸtÄ±r.\r\n\r\nAvlu KÃ¼ltÃ¼rÃ¼: KonaklarÄ±n Ã§oÄŸunda yÃ¼ksek duvarlarla Ã§evrili iÃ§ avlular bulunur. Bu avlular hem aile mahremiyetini saÄŸlar hem de sÄ±cak yaz gÃ¼nlerinde serin bir alan sunar.\r\n\r\nÄ°ÅŸlemeler: KapÄ± tokmaklarÄ±, ahÅŸap tavanlar ve pencere Ã¼stlerindeki taÅŸ oymacÄ±lÄ±ÄŸÄ±, konaÄŸÄ±n sahibinin sosyal statÃ¼sÃ¼nÃ¼ simgeleyen detaylarla doludur.\r\n\r\nGÃ¼ncel Durum:\r\nBu konaklarÄ±n bir kÄ±smÄ± hala konut olarak kullanÄ±lmakta, bir kÄ±smÄ± ise koruma altÄ±na alÄ±narak butik otel veya mÃ¼ze-ev projesi olarak deÄŸerlendirilmektedir.','','38.21245970956963','39.288305878098186','uploads/places/place_1773210800_2796.jpeg','','','',NULL,0,'2026-03-11 06:01:03','','General Information:\r\nThe mansions (Konaks) of Ã‡Ã¼ngÃ¼ÅŸ are multi-story structures dating back to the 19th and early 20th centuries. Built by wealthy local families, administrators, or merchants, these mansions are strategically constructed on terraces to harmonize with the district\'s steep and rugged terrain.\r\n\r\nArchitectural Features:\r\n\r\nMaterials: Following the tradition of DiyarbakÄ±r architecture, the primary materials used are black basalt stone and white limestone. The contrast between these two colors creates a visually striking facade.\r\n\r\nLayout: Most mansions consist of two or three floors. The lower floors typically house winter rooms, pantries, and stables, while the upper floors are designed with large windows and balconies (similar to \"eyvans\") to capture the breeze and the view.\r\n\r\nCourtyard Culture: Many of these mansions feature inner courtyards enclosed by high walls. These courtyards ensure family privacy and provide a cool sanctuary during the scorching summer months.\r\n\r\nOrnamentation: Details such as ornate door knockers, carved wooden ceilings, and intricate stone engravings above the windows represent the social status and artistic taste of the original owners.\r\n\r\nCurrent Status:\r\nWhile some of these mansions are still inhabited as private residences, others have been taken under prot