r was last analyzed on April 5, 2005, by the \"Ministry of Health Refik Saydam Hygiene Center Presidency, Environmental Health Research Directorate\" (Protocol No: 1192). According to the analysis results, the water is chemically and bacteriologically safe and beneficial for human health.\r\n\r\nThe Legend of Ã‡ermik Thermal Springs\r\nAccording to legend, the ruler of Ã‡ermik at the time had a very beautiful daughter named Melike BelkÄ±s. One day, she fell ill and developed various sores on her body. The physicians of the time made great efforts to treat her, but they could find no cure. Over time, her condition worsened to the point where her wounds became infested, emitting a foul odor so strong that no one could enter the palace.\r\n\r\nTo distance her from the palace, the ruler sent his daughter to the region where the current thermal springs are located, accompanied by guards. While wandering the area, Melike BelkÄ±s discovered a hot water source. To pass the time, she began playing with this water every day. Shortly after, it was observed that the parts of her body that came into contact with the water began to heal. Noticing the improvement, Melike BelkÄ±s bathed in this water exactly 21 times and was completely cured of her wounds.\r\n\r\nUpon seeing her full recovery, the guards joyfully reported the news to the palace. The ruler, receiving this wonderful news, went to fetch Melike BelkÄ±s with great celebration alongside the palace court. When Melike BelkÄ±s showed her father the water that had healed her, the ruler ordered his master builders to construct the bathhouse we know today as \"BÃ¼yÃ¼k PaÅŸa.\"','Inflammatory Rheumatism (Ä°ltihabi Romatizmalar)\r\n\r\nChronic Low Back Pain (Kronik Bel AÄŸrÄ±larÄ±)\r\n\r\nOsteoarthritis / Calcification (KireÃ§lenmeler)\r\n\r\nJoint Diseases (Eklem HastalÄ±klarÄ±)\r\n\r\nMuscle Pain and Muscular Rheumatism (Kas aÄŸrÄ±larÄ± ve Kas RomatizmalarÄ±)\r\n\r\nInjuries and Skin Diseases (Yaralanma ve Cilt HastalÄ±klarÄ±)\r\n\r\nSoft Tissue Diseases (YumuÅŸak Doku HastalÄ±klarÄ±)\r\n\r\nNeurological Disorders (Sinir Sistemiyle Ä°lgili HastalÄ±klar)\r\n\r\nGeneral Stress Disorders (Genel Stres BozukluklarÄ±)\r\n\r\nSports Injuries and Treatment (Spor YaralanmalarÄ± ve Tedavisi)\r\n\r\nGynecological Diseases (KadÄ±n HastalÄ±klarÄ±)\r\n\r\nOsteoporosis (Kemik Erimesi)\r\n\r\nUrinary Tract and Gallbladder Disorders (Ä°drar YollarÄ± ve Safra Kesesi RahatsÄ±zlÄ±klarÄ±)\r\n\r\nPost-Orthopedic, Brain, and Neurosurgery Recovery: Highly effective for long-term immobility following major surgeries. (Ortopedik, Beyin ve Sinir Cerrahisi sonrasÄ± uzun sÃ¼reli hareketsizlik durumlarÄ±nda etkilidir.)');
